<hr>
<div style="text-align: center;"><br>
<strong><span style="font-size:24px">NIWA News</span></strong></div>
<br>
<strong>April Fools' - </strong>For April Fools' this year, NIWA organized a collaborative prank between several of its member wikis and announced a big change: due to a falling out with Nintendo, NIWA would become "SIWA", or the Sony Independent Wiki Alliance.

<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;"><strong id="docs-internal-guid-4255e40e-c22e-4b5b-d031-8884491b4ea3"><img alt="SIWA.png" height="122" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/jLn7e_EkOfOgPyKU9Cb5C4cSu3sZfRG3RcfBArPYYB2rv24AV8XvrmrEyGSsM_BmTGt-EeaozO43NzOVT1JsFA8EFkNC3H6GhGRmyUEMUt9QfjJMNbDT1J-E0OHgbhO7fIDSIk_M" width="216" style="border: 0;height: auto !important;outline: none;text-decoration: none;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;"></strong></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;">Pikipedia became Patapedia; MarioWiki became the Crash Bandicoot Wiki; Nookipedia became Toropedia; Fire Emblem Wiki became TearRingSagaWiki; and Inkipedia became the Krillzone Wiki.<br>
<br>
<strong>The 'Shroom -</strong> The 121st issue of The 'Shroom is now available <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/The_%27Shroom:Issue_121" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">here</a>, which includes article spotlights, some fun "fake news," games, opinion pieces, and more.<br>
<br>
<strong>Discord Servers -</strong> Over the past year, several NIWA wikis have opened up their own Discord servers. If you're interested in talking with fellow fans and editors, check them out!</p>

<ul dir="ltr">
	<li style="text-align: left;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://discord.gg/pYghWh3" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">ABXY</a>&nbsp;(Strategy Wiki, MetroidWiki, Inkipedia, Wikibound, WarsWiki)</li>
	<li style="text-align: left;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="http://discord.gg/bulbagarden" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Bulbagarden / Bulbapedia</a></li>
	<li style="text-align: left;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://discord.gg/012STZhzAArYV2ESy" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Fire Emblem Wiki</a></li>
	<li style="text-align: left;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://nookipedia.com/wiki/Nookipedia:Discord" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Nookipedia</a></li>
	<li style="text-align: left;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://www.ssbwiki.com/SmashWiki:Discord_server" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Smash Wiki</a></li>
	<li style="text-align: left;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="http://discord.gg/zelda" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Zelda Universe / ZeldaWiki</a></li>
</ul>

<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;"><strong>Promotions - </strong>April saw four new promotions&nbsp;among NIWA wikis! Congrats to <a href="https://splatoonwiki.org/wiki/User:Kjhf" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">kjhf</a> for his promotion to a bureaucrat on Inkipedia; <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/User:Alex95" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Alex95</a> for his promotion to a patroller on Super Mario Wiki; <a href="http://zelda.gamepedia.com/UserProfile:Molldust" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Molldust</a> for their promotion to an administrator of Zelda Wiki; and finally, <a href="http://zelda.gamepedia.com/User:Link_Lab" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Link Lab</a> for his promotion to Deputy Director of Zelda Wiki.<br>
&nbsp;</p>

<hr>
<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;">&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;"><strong><span style="font-size:24px">Nintendo News</span></strong></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;"><br>
<strong>New Console - </strong>Nintendo has announced the New 2DS XL! Releasing in June in Australia and in July for the rest of the world,&nbsp;the clamshell device starts at $149 USD and features sleek bezels, amiibo support, and advanced controls (C-stick along with ZL and ZR buttons). Learn more <a href="https://www.nintendo.com/2ds/new-nintendo-2ds/" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">on Nintendo's official website</a>.</p>

<div style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.nintendo.com/2ds/new-nintendo-2ds/" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><strong id="docs-internal-guid-4255e40e-c22f-649f-5ea6-34dc9672646f"><img height="269" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/79ytS5Ydx_0U0KJNCbiv_3NK2aWg6z40vdZV_AFJWjhd4i11jwPfl6AA0nAcLFfQcZVTqu9CWLKLpBKwE6w8FxVMYnbRXyO2ar55fa7THhWWop0hvLRa5-1v3f3kcBgI3hwsfOyF" style="border: 0px initial;width: 250px;height: 269px;margin: 0px;outline: none;text-decoration: none;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" width="250"></strong></a></div>

<p dir="ltr" style="margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;text-align: left;"><strong>Nintendo Direct Updates - </strong>A <a href="http://www.nintendo.com/nintendo-direct/04-12-2017/#/video-1ndirect" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Nintendo Direct presentation</a> was held on on April 12, bringing with it news regarding upcoming Nintendo Switch and Nintendo 3DS titles. Among this news was the announcement of the<a href="https://www.ssbwiki.com/Amiibo#Wave_10" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"> final six <em>Super Smash Bros.</em> series amiibo</a>, three new <a href="http://zelda.gamepedia.com/Amiibo#The_Legend_of_Zelda_amiibo" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>The Legend of Zelda</em> series amiibo</a>, and release dates for <a href="http://www.niwanetwork.org/wiki/ARMS" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>Arms</em></a>&nbsp;and <a href="https://splatoonwiki.org/wiki/Splatoon_2" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>Splatoon 2</em></a>.</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;"><a href="https://www.ssbwiki.com/Amiibo#Wave_10" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><img height="303" src="https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/thumb/4/4e/Bayonetta_amiibo.png/594px-Bayonetta_amiibo.png" style="border: 0px;width: 300px;height: 303px;margin: 0px;outline: none;text-decoration: none;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" width="300"></a><br>
The upcoming <a href="https://www.ssbwiki.com/Bayonetta_(SSB4)" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Bayonetta</a> amiibo, releasing worldwide on July 21.</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;text-align: left;"><br>
<strong>Strong Start - </strong><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Mario_Kart_8_Deluxe" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>Mario Kart 8 Deluxe</em></a> came out worldwide for the Nintendo Switch just a few days ago. The game has received critical acclaim for its improvements on the Wii U's <em>Mario Kart 8</em>, and is already the top-selling video game of the year so far on Amazon.<br>
<br>
<strong>Switch Stats - </strong>The Nintendo Switch has seen a strong start; as of March 31, 2017, the company has sold 2.74 million Switch units worldwide. Nintendo has predicted that it will ship 10 million more consoles as well as 35 million games in the next year.</p>
&nbsp;

<hr>&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;"><span style="font-size:24px"><strong>Recent &amp; Upcoming Releases</strong></span></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;text-align: left;"><br>
<strong>Nintendo Switch</strong></p>

<ul dir="ltr">
	<li style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><em><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Mario_Kart_8_Deluxe" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Mario Kart 8 Deluxe</a>&nbsp;</em><span style="font-size:12px">(Worldwide: April 28)&nbsp;</span></li>
	<li style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minecraft" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>Minecraft: Nintendo Switch Edition</em></a><em>&nbsp;</em><span style="font-size:12px">(NA: May 11 |&nbsp;EU: May 12)&nbsp;</span></li>
	<li style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disgaea_5" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>Disgaea 5 Complete</em></a><em>&nbsp;</em><span style="font-size:12px">(JP: March 3 | NA: May 23&nbsp;| PAL:&nbsp;May 26)&nbsp;</span></li>
	<li style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultra_Street_Fighter_II:_The_Final_Challengers" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #2BAADF;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;"><em>Ultra Street Fighter II: The Final Challengers</em></a><em>&nbsp;</em><span style="font-size:12px">(Worldwide: May 26)&nbsp;</span></li>
</ul>

